quran[6]{c,v,t,f}:
  2,94,"Say, [O Muḥammad], "
  2,95,"But never will they wish for it, ever, because of what their hands have put forth. And Allāh is Knowing of the wrongdoers."
  2,96,"And you will surely find them the most greedy of people for life - [even] more than those who associate others with Allāh. One of them wishes that he could be granted life a thousand years, but it would not remove him in the least from the [coming] punishment that he should be granted life. And Allāh is Seeing of what they do."
  3,34,"Descendants, some of them from others. And Allāh is Hearing and Knowing."
  3,35,"[Mention, O Muḥammad], when the wife of ʿImrān said, "
  3,36,"But when she delivered her, she said, "